LaTeX Mathematics to Image Converter (LaMatIC)
----------------------------------------------

This tool helps you to generate beautiful mathematics snippets for your e.g. PowerPoint presentation without
the need to use the builtin tools for that. You can e.g. just copy & paste from your research paper
tex onto the CLI to generate a high quality PNG image from it.


Requirements
------------

  o Ruby
  o GNU/Linux System
  o LaTeX (tex2dvi, dvips)
  o Imagemagick (covnert)


Examples
--------

% ./LaTeX_PNG_Generator.rb -f white -g "W_k = \sum\limits_{r=1}^{k} \sum\limits_{i,i' \in C_r} d_{ii'}  \\ \forall r \in [1,k]"

Development
-----------

% rake -T 
(in /home/br/projects/Battery)
  rake all                 # Default Task - Run cucumber and rspec with rcov
  rake clean               # Clean up temporary data
  rake cucumber            # Run Cucumber features
  rake flay                # Flay the code
  rake flog                # Flog the code
  rake rcov:all            # Run both specs and features to generate aggregated coverage
  rake rcov:clobber_rspec  # Remove rcov products for rspec
  rake rcov:cucumber       # Run Cucumber features
  rake rcov:rspec          # Run specs using RCov
  rake yardoc              # Generate Yardoc documentation


Code Quality
------------

Current code quality is kind of hack status. This needs severe improvement with rspec, cucumber etc.


